    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION CARRIERS: ROCKWELL - GENERAL PROCEDURES - INSTALL NEW DRI-LOC FASTENERS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1400619" svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL NEW DRI-LOC FASTENERS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the oil and dirt from threaded holes. There is no special cleaning required.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble parts using new Dri-Loc fasteners.</para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not apply adhesives or sealants on new Dri-Loc fasteners or in the threaded holes. If other
                        adhesives or sealants are used, the new Dri-Loc adhesive will not function correctly.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the Dri-Loc fasteners to the required torque value for that size fastener. Refer to
                the
                <hotlnk document="s14006t_57.xml" xrefid="hl1400608">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>There is no drying time required for Dri-Loc fasteners.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
